Christmas box
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:In NZ use much wider and friendlier than OED2 sense of usu. money tips and gratuities given to postmen, etc, `and hence, vulgarly and in dial. use it is often equivalent to "Christmas present"'; or P8: `low coll. (and dial.)'. It can now mean any Christmas present whether given to family, or to workpeople as a Christmas tip.
Origin:[none]
